				<td colspan="2"><span>Hey gang im a 57 bard learning my AOE skillz. I have been AE kiting dulaks since 44 or so using Autocircle. Stopped around 55 started broading my horizons. Problem i come into play with is Mobs being to big for a Autocircle. Ive tried PoV I can autocircle there, but takes 4 forevers and a day. My question is What am i missing with Manual Kiting. Ive seen bards kite say PoN half the zone trees and all and they are AE kiting them all. I can't  seem to stay outta reach of the darn trees. I run straight take a turn to get in reach of my AE and get hit. Ive practiced with just one tree time and time again and can't get it down. I have a Lute of the Howler and a Engraved Spiral Shell Conch. I have tried no selos. Selos with Brass Selos with TDok Walrus BDMG. NO luck getting outta range. Even with Just selos and  brass  im way to fast and thats with Run turned off. 
<br />
Now, I have read thru the post and all i can see is people talking about AUtocircle. Well i got ruined on Autocircle and just want to learn the other ways out there for instances like Bigger mobs. 
<br />
Seeing other Bards do the deed leaves me to believe i should be able to do what they do. Is there some AA&quot;s im missing are you using just Run 3. How do you get withing 30' of a mob and not get pummled, on bigger mobs. Sorry for the long post, but I have been reading on this for some time, and don't see just a Manual Kite post out there. Someone come to my aide please im begging ya <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
